<title>ITALY: Italy's Genoa sees June CPI at 0.1 pct mo/mo.</title>
<headline>Italy's Genoa sees June CPI at 0.1 pct mo/mo.</headline>
<dateline>GENOA, Italy 1997-06-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Italian city of Genoa said its June consumer price index stood at 0.1 percent month on month and 0.8 percent year on year.</p>
<p>In May, Genoa's inflation rate was 0.2 percent month on month and 0.5 percent year on year.</p>
<p>Genoa is one of 11 Italian cities publishing inflation data on Friday and Monday. The city's CPI has a weighting of 2.88 percent on the national index. The 11 sample cities have a combined weighting of 75.66 percent on the total index.  </p>
<p>The following is the breakdown of the price changes.</p>
<p>(figures in brackets refer to May 1997):</p>
<p>					    Month/Month     Year/Year</p>
<p>    General index		     0.1   (0.2)     0.8   (0.5)</p>
<p>    Food				 -0.4   (0.3)    -2.1  (-1.5)</p>
<p>    Clothing and footwear	   0.0   (0.1)     2.5   (2.5)</p>
<p>    Housing and utility charges   0.0   (0.0)     4.3   (4.2)</p>
<p>    Furniture			   0.0   (0.3)     0.6   (0.6)</p>
<p>    Health services		   0.2   (0.1)     2.5   (2.3)</p>
<p>    Transportation		    0.0   (0.2)     0.7   (0.8)</p>
<p>    Entertainment and culture     0.1  (-0.6)     0.0  (-1.1)</p>
<p>    Education			   0.0   (0.0)     3.6   (3.6)</p>
<p>    Hotels and restaurants	  0.7   (0.0)     1.1   (0.4)</p>
<p>    Other goods or services	 0.3   (1.2)    -0.3  (-1.3)</p>
